	You are in a dark room. You see a candle on the table. What do you do?

a) Pick up the candle.
b) Blow out the candle.		You blow out the candle and die from insanity.
c) Eat the candle.		You are poisoned by the candle and die.
	
	You pick up the candle and walk forward. You hit a wall. It is the wall part of a hall. Which way do you go?

a) Right.
b) Left.		You walk to the left and fall into a hole full of rusty spikes and die instantly.

	You walk to the right and are greeted with a door with a rusty lock. What do you do?

a) Try to smash the lock.		You smash the lock and a sharp part impales your foot through your shoe and you die of tetanus.
b) Try to open the door.

	The door opens easily with a small squeek. You walk through and you end up in a small room. There is a mouse on the ground in the middle of the room. What do you do?

a) Kill the mouse.		You kill the mouse and suddenly more mice crawl through the cracks of the stone walls and eat you alive.
b) Touch the mouse.		You touch the mouse and die from disease.
c) Place the candle in front of the mouse.		You place the candle in front of the mouse and it eats the candle. You die from insanity.
d) Take a nap.

	You take a nap. You wake up a short while later and notice that the mouse is gone. In its place is a man facing away from you. What do you do?

a) Kill the man.
b) Talk to the man.		As you attempt to talk to the man, he turns around and his face is covered in blood. He lunges at you and kills you.

	You killed the man. The walls collapse. You are in a wheat field. You have won text_based_game.
